Available is a master bed / bath / walk-in closet in a 2 br / 2.5 bath townhome that borders the historic Irvington neighborhood in NE Portland.
This room has it all. Enough space to fit a king size bed, a full size desk, dressers, night stands. Basically, I`ve seen apartments in New York the size of this living space. The bedroom has several dimensions (can`t measure it right now due to a tape measure that seemed to grow a pair of legs), but when I say big... I mean BIG. The first comment people make when they walk in is usually, "Whoa!"
Yes, the wall color is white, but you can paint it as you see fit. (Landlord will require you to repaint to the original color).
The walk-in closet is also huge. Not only does it feature 2 layers of hanging space, there`s even a little wrap around cubby that fits more storage and has an extra shelf. It`s like that little bonus storage you never knew existed! You also will have a couple of shoe racks left in the closet to use.
The bathroom is pretty spacious too. Standard shower tub, sink and toilet. There`s a built-in shelf and towel rack over the toilet, that I will leave. It also has a medicine cabinet and plenty of storage under the sink. Standard shower curtain and liner works.
About the place.
I have lived in various neighborhoods but can now say that I wouldn`t want to live anywhere else in Portland. The neighborhood is quiet (many neighbors keep to themselves) and off the main street (so even with Nike`s big sales, you don`t get a lot of noise). There`s never been any crime on the street since I`ve lived here. You can go for a run up through Irvington and look at the giant homes on a pretty flat stretch of sidewalk. On your bike, it`s a 10 minute ride to the heart of Alberta, N Williams, and maybe a 10-15 minute ride to Mississippi or the Pearl. You will love how centrally located you are for the price and what you get for your money.
The downstairs features wood floors (yes, that`s different from the pictures). It`s a cherry hue Pergo floor and looks nice with the current wall paint. There`s a gas fireplace, a back patio with gas grill, and even a little wine closet under the stairs (Or you could use it for additional storage). The kitchen is pretty standard. You have plenty of cabinet space for dishes, glassware, silverware, cookware and storage. There`s also a butler`s pantry for extra storage right next to the kitchen.
Downstairs also features a half bath with a washer and dryer. The washer is an older model and works great. The dryer was replaced 2 years ago and hasn`t had any issues.
The townhome also features a garage. We used to house a car in there, but a previous tenant left a bunch of stuff behind (extra refrigerator and furniture that never got cleaned out), so it may be tough to fit a car in there, but there remains plenty of storage space.
You`ll be responsible for utilities (Cable, gas, electric) which runs about $120 a month. Every 3 months is the Portland Water & Sewer bill which will tack on about $100 to your bill. The landlord pays for trash service. Trash comes every other Tuesday. Recycling comes every Tuesday.
I hope to start meeting potential housemates Sunday and Monday. The room will be available August 15 (there might be a few days wiggle room if necessary). Please send me an e-mail including a little about yourself, your schedule and when you might like to meet. I look forward to hearing from you!
